The Dow Jones Industrial Average is climbing Wednesday afternoon with shares of Pfizer and 3M leading the way for the blue-chip average. Shares of Pfizer PFE, -0.48% and 3M MMM, -0.03% have contributed to the index's intraday rally, as the Dow DJIA, +0.52% is trading 162 points (0.6%) higher. Pfizer's shares have gained $1.10 (3.3%) while those of 3M have risen $3.65, or 2.5%, combining for an approximately 32-point boost for the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the gain include Walgreens Boots WBA, -3.09%, Apple Inc. AAPL, +3.70%, and Boeing BA, +0.10%. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components results in a 6.78-point swing.

